28 // Reading arguments, groups, etc.
29 
30 // There are two parameters that control what happens in case
31 // an outer cmd or a \par is seen.
32 // If scanner_status is ss_normal then an outer command is valid
33 // If long_state is ls_long then a \par command is valid
34 // A \par in a non-long macro or an outer command in an argument aborts expansion.
35 
36 // scanner_status = ss_macro holds when expanding a macro
37 // scanner_status = ss_matching when reading arguments of a C++ macro
38 // in all other cases long_state should be ls_long
39 
40 // The next command is called when get_token sees EOF or an outer command
41 // does nothing if scanner_status is ss_normal
42 // otherwise signals an error depending on the value of this quantity.
43 // May insert a brace or \fi or \par
44 // May change long_state to ls_bad
45 // Replaces offending token by space
46 
47 void Parser::check_outer_validity() {
48  Buffer &B = err_buf;
49  B.reset();
50  switch (scanner_status) {
51  case ss_skipping:
52  B << "Incomplete \\if? missing \\fi inserted\n";
53  back_input(hash_table.fi_token);
54  break;
55  case ss_defining:
56  B << "Runaway definition?\n";
57  back_input(hash_table.CB_token);
58  break;
59  case ss_absorbing:
60  B << "Runaway text?\n";
61  back_input(hash_table.CB_token);
62  break;
63  case ss_macro:
64  B << "Runaway argument?\n";
65  long_state = ls_bad;
66  back_input(hash_table.par_token);
67  break;
68  default: // matching
69  B << "Runaway argument?\n";
70  }
71  if (cur_cmd_chr.cmd == eof_marker_cmd)
72  B << "End of file";
73  else
74  B << "Forbidden control sequence " << cur_tok.tok_to_str();
75  if (scanner_status == ss_skipping)
76  B << " in conditional started at line " << conditions.top_line();
77  else {
78  B << " found while scanning ";
79  if (scanner_status == ss_defining)
80  B << "definition";
81  else if (scanner_status == ss_absorbing)
82  B << "text";
83  else // ss_matching or ss_macro
84  B << "use";
85  B << " of " << err_tok.tok_to_str();
86  }
87  signal_error(err_tok, "Runaway argument");
88  if (cur_cmd_chr.cmd == eof_marker_cmd) return;
89  cur_tok = hash_table.space_token;
90  cur_cmd_chr = CmdChr(space_catcode, subtypes(' '));
91 }

96 // Adjusts the brace counter b. Returns true if it becomes 0.
97 // The scanner returns only balanced lists.
98 auto Parser::check_brace(int &b) -> bool {
99  if (cur_tok.is_a_brace()) {
100  if (cur_tok.is_a_left_brace())
101  b++;
102  else {
103  b--;
104  if (b == 0) return true;
105  }
106  }
107  return false;
108 }
109 
110 // Assumes an open brace has been read. Reads in res everything up to the
111 // matching close brace. Returns true in case of error (cl is start line).
112 auto Parser::scan_group0(TokenList &res, int cl) -> bool {
113  int b = 1; // brace counter, we start with 1
114  for (;;) {
115  if (get_token()) {
116  missing_close_brace(cl);
117  return true;
118  }
119  if (check_brace(b)) return false;
120  if (cur_tok == hash_table.par_token && long_state != ls_long) {
121  if (long_state == ls_bad)
122  long_state = ls_normal;
123  else
124  runaway(cl);
125  return true;
126  }
127  if (cur_cmd_chr.cmd == eof_marker_cmd) return true;
128  res.push_back(cur_tok);
129  }
130 }
131 
132 // Same as the function above, but with one argument less
133 void Parser::skip_group0(TokenList &L) { scan_group0(L, get_cur_line()); }
134 
135 // Assumes an open brace has been read. Like skip_group0, returns nothing.
136 // Used by ignore_arg, assumes scanner_status==ss_skipping
137 void Parser::scan_ignore_group() {
138  int cl = get_cur_line();
139  int b = 1;
140  for (;;) {
141  if (get_token()) {
142  missing_close_brace(cl);
143  return;
144  }
145  if (check_brace(b)) return;
146  if (cur_tok == hash_table.par_token && long_state != ls_long) {
147  runaway(cl);
148  return;
149  }
150  }
151 }

153 // In the case of \edef, all tokens are expanded, unless they come from the
154 // \the or a protected command; these are appended to L by this procedure.
155 // Returns true if EOF; otherwise cur_tok holds the next token
156 auto Parser::edef_aux(TokenList &L) -> bool {
157  for (;;) {
158  if (get_token()) return true;
159  if (!cur_cmd_chr.is_expandable()) return false;
160  if (cur_cmd_chr.is_protected()) return false;
161  if (cur_cmd_chr.cmd != the_cmd)
162  expand();
163  else {
164  Token T = cur_tok;
165  TokenList q = E_the(cur_cmd_chr.chr);
166  if (tracing_commands()) the_log << lg_start << T << "->" << q << "." << lg_end;
167  L.splice(L.end(), q);
168  }
169  }
170 }

172 // Same as scan_group0, tokens may be expanded if exp is true
173 // We are reading a macro body with N arguments, so that #1 must be interpreted.
174 // par tokens are allowed, no runaway test
175 
176 void Parser::scan_group3(TokenList &res, int cl, bool exp, size_t N) {
177  int b = 1;
178  for (;;) {
179  bool stop = exp ? edef_aux(res) : get_token();
180  if (stop) {
181  missing_close_brace(cl);
182  return;
183  }
184  if (check_brace(b)) return;
185  if (cur_cmd_chr.is_parameter()) after_parameter(exp, N);
186  res.push_back(cur_tok);
187  }
188 }
189 
190 // special case of scan_group3, with exp=true, N=0,
191 // but there is no closing brace: we read until end of data.
192 // Thus check_brace() should not yield true
193 
194 void Parser::scan_group4(TokenList &res, int cl) {
195  int b = 1;
196  for (;;) {
197  if (edef_aux(res)) {
198  if (b != 1) missing_close_brace(cl);
199  return;
200  }
201  if (check_brace(b)) {
202  parse_error(err_tok, "Too many closing braces");
203  return;
204  }
205  res.push_back(cur_tok);
206  }
207 }

209 // Used in case of scan_group_del or scan_group_del1
210 // Contribute a group or a single token to the list res.
211 // Returns true in case of error.
212 // Invariant b=-1 is res is empty, b=0 if it contains a single group, b>0 otherwise
213 
214 auto Parser::scan_group1(TokenList &res, int &b, int cl) -> bool {
215  Token aux = cur_tok;
216  if (aux.is_OB_token()) {
217  res.push_back(cur_tok); // Insert the opening brace
218  if (scan_group0(res, cl)) {
219  res.push_back(hash_table.CB_token); // Insert the closing brace
220  return true;
221  }
222  res.push_back(cur_tok);
223  b++;
224  return false;
225  }
226  if (aux.is_CB_token()) {
227  extra_close_brace(cl);
228  return true;
229  }
230  if (aux == hash_table.par_token && long_state != ls_long) {
231  if (long_state == ls_bad)
232  long_state = ls_normal;
233  else
234  runaway(cl);
235  return true;
236  }
237  b = 2;
238  res.push_back(aux);
239  return false;
240 }

242 // In the case of \foo {x} and \foo x, this command reads an optional space
243 // reduces the second case to the first one, and reads an open brace.
244 // Returns true in case of error. Is used in math mode. Normal arguments
245 // are read via
246 // if(!before_mac_arg()) skip_group0(L);
247 // or optimised version: scan_group2(L)
248 
249 auto Parser::before_mac_arg() -> bool {
250  for (;;) {
251  if (get_token()) {
252  runaway(-1);
253  return true;
254  }
255  if (cur_tok.is_space_token()) continue;
256  if (cur_tok.is_OB_token()) return false;
257  if (cur_tok.is_CB_token()) {
258  parse_error(err_tok, "Missing { inserted before unexpected } in argument of ", err_tok, "", "extra}");
259  back_input(cur_tok);
260  return true;
261  }
262  back_input(hash_table.CB_token);
263  back_input(cur_tok);
264  return false;
265  }
266 }

268 // Inner code of read_arg. This is the command that reads an argument;
269 // note that outer braces disappear
270 auto Parser::scan_group2(TokenList &L) -> bool {
271  int cl = get_cur_line();
272  for (;;) {
273  if (get_token()) {
274  runaway(-1);
275  return true;
276  }
277  if (cur_tok.is_space_token()) continue;
278  if (cur_tok.is_OB_token()) return scan_group0(L, cl);
279  if (cur_tok.is_CB_token()) { // the message is stange ...
280  parse_error(err_tok, "Missing { inserted before unexpected } in argument of ", err_tok, "", "extra}");
281  return true;
282  }
283  if (cur_tok == hash_table.par_token && long_state != ls_long) {
284  if (long_state == ls_bad)
285  long_state = ls_normal;
286  else
287  runaway(cl);
288  return true;
289  }
290  L.push_back(cur_tok);
291  return false;
292  }
293 }

295 // Special case of read_delimited, in case a single token is wanted.
296 // Gathers all tokens until finding x
297 // A newline token is identified with a space token.
298 // If this is a group (b==0), then outer braces will be removed;
299 auto Parser::scan_group_del1(TokenList &res, Token x) -> bool {
300  int cl = get_cur_line();
301  int b = -1;
302  for (;;) {
303  if (get_token()) {
304  bad_delimited(cl, x);
305  return true;
306  }
307  if (x.is_same_token(cur_tok)) break;
308  if (scan_group1(res, b, cl)) return true;
309  }
310  if (b == 0) { // Remove external braces
311  res.pop_back();
312  res.pop_front();
313  }
314  return false;
315 }
316 
317 // reads a token list R followed by L (which is discarded).
318 // At every stage we check that L is present; if not so, a token or a group is read
319 // outer braces are removed if possible.
320 auto Parser::scan_group_del(TokenList &res, const TokenList &L) -> bool {
321  int cl = get_cur_line();
322  int b = -1;
323  for (;;) {
324  // First check if L is found
325  TokenList backup;
326  auto C = L.begin();
327  auto E = L.end();
328  for (;;) {
329  if (C == E) { // ok found
330  if (b == 0) {
331  res.pop_back();
332  res.pop_front();
333  }
334  return false;
335  }
336  Token x = *C;
337  ++C;
338  if (get_token()) { // EOF abort
339  bad_delimited(cl, Token(0));
340  return true;
341  }
342  backup.push_back(cur_tok);
343  if (x.is_same_token(cur_tok)) continue;
344  back_input(backup);
345  break;
346  }
347  if (get_token()) {
348  bad_delimited(cl, Token(0));
349  return true;
350  }
351  if (scan_group1(res, b, cl)) return true;
352  }
353 }

355 // Reads the tokens of the list L
356 // in the case below, a closing brace is inserted so that no runaway is signaled.
357 // \def\tfoo a{} \edef\xx{\tfoo}
358 auto Parser::skip_prefix(const TokenList &L) -> bool {
359  auto C = L.begin();
360  auto E = L.end();
361  while (C != E) {
362  Token T = *C;
363  ++C;
364  get_token();
365  if (cur_tok.is_CB_token()) back_input();
366  if (!T.is_same_token(cur_tok)) {
367  bad_macro_prefix(cur_tok, T);
368  return true;
369  }
370  }
371  return false;
372 }

374 // Reads a LaTeX optional argument, enclosed in brackets
375 // Initial spaces are discarded. Return false in no bracket found
376 auto Parser::scan_group_opt(TokenList &L, bool &have_arg) -> bool {
377  for (;;) {
378  if (get_token()) return true;
379  if (cur_tok.is_space_token()) continue;
380  if (cur_tok.is_open_bracket()) {
381  have_arg = true;
382  return scan_group_del1(L, Token(other_t_offset, ']'));
383  }
384  back_input();
385  return false;
386  }
387 }

396 auto Parser::read_optarg(TokenList &L) -> bool {
397  scanner_status = ss_matching;
398  bool retval = false;
399  scan_group_opt(L, retval);
400  scanner_status = ss_normal;
401  return retval;

469 auto Parser::read_token_arg(int cl) -> bool {
470  TokenList L;
471  for (;;) {
472  if (get_token()) {
473  runaway(-1);
474  return true;
475  }
476  if (cur_tok.is_space_token()) continue;
477  if (cur_tok.is_OB_token()) {
478  scan_group0(L, cl);
479  if (L.size() == 1) {
480  back_input(L);
481  get_token();
482  return false;
483  }
484  err_one_arg(L);
485  return true;
486  }
487  if (cur_tok.is_CB_token()) {
488  parse_error(err_tok, "Extra } ignored", "extra}");
489  return true;
490  }
491  return false;
492  }
493 }

495 // Paragraphs are forbidden in ignored arguments
496 // Use read_arg() if \par allowed
497 void Parser::ignore_arg() {
498  SaveLongState sth(ls_normal);
499  scanner_status = ss_matching;
500  skip_initial_space();
501  if (cur_tok.is_invalid())
502  runaway(-1);
503  else if (cur_tok.is_OB_token())
504  scan_ignore_group();
505  scanner_status = ss_normal;
506 }

508 // In a case like \def\bar#1foo#2{...}, this returns the value of #1
509 // given the token list foo as argument.

511 auto Parser::read_delimited(const TokenList &L) -> TokenList {
512  TokenList res;

519 // Reads the body of a \def ou \xdef. A space is skipped,
520 // and an open brace is read first.
521 void Parser::read_mac_body(TokenList &L, bool exp, size_t N) {
522  scanner_status = ss_defining;
523  skip_initial_space();
524  if (cur_cmd_chr.is_open_brace())
525  scan_group3(L, get_cur_line(), exp, N);
526  else
527  missing_open_brace();
528  scanner_status = ss_normal;
529 }

531 // This is like scan_toks(false,true) in TeX; but the token list has already been
532 // read.
533 // This feeds the list L to the body of an edef.
534 // The expansion of L will be in L. The loop stops at the end of L
535 // at brace_level zero (b=1)
536 void Parser::read_toks_edef(TokenList &L) {
537  scanner_status = ss_absorbing;
538  SaveState sv_state;
539  save_the_state(sv_state); // now TL is empty
540  restricted = true;
541  TL.swap(L); // now L is empty
542  scan_group4(L, get_cur_line()); // This fills L
543  restore_the_state(sv_state);
544  scanner_status = ss_normal;
545 }

572 // Returns true if the next line contains \end{env}
573 // In this case, removes the \end{env}
574 auto Parser::is_verbatim_end() -> bool {
575  file_ended = false;
576  if (at_eol()) get_a_new_line();
577  if (file_ended) return false;
578  bool res = input_buffer.contains_env(get_cur_env_name().c_str());
579  if (res) {
580  if (input_buffer.head() == 0)
581  kill_line();
582  else { // remove chars from input_line
583  auto n = input_line.size();
584  for (size_t i = 0; i < n; i++)
585  if (input_line[i] == '}') {
586  input_line_pos = i + 1;
587  break;
588  }
589  }
590  }
591  return res;
592 }

594 // Reads all characters until finding test; most character have catcode 12
595 // but some non-letters have catcode 11. result is \verbatimprefix{\verbatim foo},
596 // pushed at the end of L (or with prefix \verbprefix pushed at the start of L).
597 // Returns true in case of problem
598 
599 auto Parser::vb_tokens(codepoint test, TokenList &L, bool before) -> bool {
600  TokenList res;
601  state = state_M;
602  for (;;) {
603  if (at_eol()) return true;
604  codepoint c = get_next_char();
605  if (c == test) break;
606  res.push_back(verbatim_chars[c.value]);
607  }
608  if (res.empty() && !before) res.push_back(hash_table.tilda_token);
609  res.push_front(hash_table.verbatim_font);
610  brace_me(res);
611  if (before)
612  res.push_front(hash_table.verb_prefix_token);
613  else
614  res.push_front(hash_table.verbatim_prefix_token);
615  if (before)
616  L.splice(L.begin(), res);
617  else
618  L.splice(L.end(), res);
619  return false;
620 }

622 // A number N gives: {\verbatimnumberfont{N}}\space
623 void token_ns::add_verbatim_number(TokenList &L, const Hashtab &H, long n) {
624  L.push_back(H.OB_token);
625  L.push_back(H.verbatim_number_font);
626  L.push_back(H.OB_token);
627  push_back_i(L, n);
628  L.push_back(H.CB_token);
629  L.push_back(H.CB_token);
630  L.push_back(H.space_token);
631 }

633 // Case of \begin{verbatim} and variants.
634 // Locally sets \endlinechar to CR, and reads each line via vb_tokens
635 void Parser::T_verbatim(int my_number, Token style, Token pre, Token post) {
636  TokenList res;
637  kill_line();
638  Token par = hash_table.par_token;
639  Token noindent = hash_table.noindent_token;
640  auto cc = eqtb_int_table[endlinechar_code].val;
641  eqtb_int_table[endlinechar_code].set_val('\r');
642 
643  bool ok = true;
644  bool want_number = false;
645  long n = 0;
646  if (my_number >= 0) {
647  my_number += count_reg_offset;
648  n = eqtb_int_table[to_unsigned(my_number)].val;
649  want_number = true;
650  }
651  int cl = get_cur_line();
652  for (;;) {
653  if (is_verbatim_end()) break;
654  if (file_ended) {
655  ok = false;
656  break;
657  }
658  // add \par\noindent before each line
659  res.push_back(par);
660  res.push_back(noindent);
661  n++;
662  if (want_number) {
663  word_define(to_unsigned(my_number), n, true);
664  token_ns::add_verbatim_number(res, hash_table, n);
665  }
666  if (vb_tokens(codepoint('\r'), res, false)) {
667  ok = false;
668  break;
669  }
670  }
671  if (!ok) bad_end_env(cl);
672  eqtb_int_table[endlinechar_code].set_val(cc); // restore
673  // pop save stack
674  cur_tok.kill();
675  pop_level(bt_env);
676  if (style != hash_table.relax_token) res.push_front(style);
677  if (pre != hash_table.relax_token) res.push_front(pre);
678  if (post != hash_table.relax_token) res.push_back(post);
679  remove_initial_space_and_back_input();
680  if (cur_cmd_chr.cmd != par_cmd) { // add final \par\noindent
681  res.push_back(par);
682  res.push_back(noindent);
683  }
684  if (tracing_commands()) the_log << lg_startbrace << "Verbatim tokens: " << res << lg_endbrace;
685  back_input(res);
686 }

688 // Caller of the previous. There could be an optional argument, a list to be
689 // interpreted. Needs to be completed.
690 
691 void Parser::T_verbatim() {
692  bool extended = cur_cmd_chr.chr == one_code;
693  bool noparse = cur_cmd_chr.chr == two_code;
694  bool optional = false;
695  if (extended || noparse) {
696  // do not read the next line (unless we have a % here)
697  for (;;) {
698  if (get_token()) break;
699  if (cur_tok.is_open_bracket()) {
700  optional = true;
701  back_input();
702  break;
703  }
704  if (cur_tok.is_only_space_token()) continue; // ok for space, not newline.
705  back_input();
706  break;
707  }
708  }
709  // Now, we know if we have an optional argument.
710  TokenList largs;
711  if (optional) read_optarg(largs);
712  std::string hook = get_cur_env_name() + "@hook";
713  if (noparse) {
714  Token t1 = hash_table.locate(hook);
715  new_macro(largs, t1, true); // definition is outside env
716  Token t2 = hash_table.locate("FV@style@lst");
717  Token t3 = hash_table.locate("FV@pre@lst");
718  Token t4 = hash_table.locate("FV@post@lst");
719  T_verbatim(-1, t2, t3, t4);
720  return;
721  }
722  TokenList lopt = get_mac_value(hook);
723  largs.push_back(hash_table.comma_token);
724  largs.splice(largs.end(), lopt);
725  std::string args = to_stringE(largs);
726  bool want_number = false;
727  SpecialHash S(args);
728  // Check if numbering wanted
729  if (!S.find("numbers").empty()) want_number = true;
730  if (!extended && numbered_verbatim) want_number = true;
731  bool reset = true;
732  if (!extended) reset = false;
733  // Check if a register number is given
734  int reg_number = S.find_counter();
735  if (reg_number >= 0) reset = false;
736  // Check if a start number is given
737  int n = 0;
738  std::string w = S.find("firstnumber");
739  if (w.empty())
740  n = 1;
741  else if (w == "last") {
742  reset = false;
743  want_number = true;
744  } else if (tralics_ns::only_digits(w)) {
745  reset = true;
746  n = atoi(w.c_str());
747  want_number = true;
748  } else {
749  reset = true;
750  n = 0;
751  }
752  if (want_number && reg_number < 0) reg_number = 21; // hardcoded
753  if (reset) word_define(to_unsigned(reg_number + count_reg_offset), n - 1, true);
754  Token t2 = hash_table.relax_token;
755  Token t3 = hash_table.relax_token;
756  Token t4 = hash_table.relax_token;
757  std::string w2 = S.find("style");
758  std::string w3 = S.find("pre");
759  if (!w2.empty()) t2 = hash_table.locate("FV@style@" + w2);
760  if (!w3.empty()) t3 = hash_table.locate("FV@pre@" + w3);
761  if (!w3.empty()) t4 = hash_table.locate("FV@post@" + w3);
762  T_verbatim(reg_number, t2, t3, t4);
763 }

793 // In the case of \verb+foo+, reads and returns the + character.
794 // Sets special_space to true if spaces have to be treaded specially
795 // Returns null in case of error
796 auto Parser::delimiter_for_verb(bool &special_space) -> codepoint {
797  codepoint t = get_next_char();

804 // In the case of \SaveVerb{ok}+foo+, reads and returns the + character,
805 // which must have spacial_catcode. returns 0 in case of trouble
806 auto Parser::delimiter_for_saveverb() -> codepoint {
807  for (;;) {
808  if (at_eol()) return codepoint();
809  codepoint c = get_next_char();
810  if (c == 0) return c;
811  if (c.is_big()) return codepoint();
812  if (get_catcode(c.value) == space_catcode) continue;
813  if (get_catcode(c.value) == special_catcode) return c;
814  return codepoint();
815  }

818 // Case of the \verb command (t=0) or |foo|, where t is the char
819 void Parser::T_verb(codepoint t) {
820  Token T = cur_tok;

866 // \begin{comment}...\end{comment} or \begin{rawxml}...\end{rawxml}
867 // The env macro will read the \end{...}, so that we pop the stack.
868 // we make sure that reading is not from a token list
869 // Ignores everything, until end of environment.
870 // or take it verbatim
871 auto Parser::T_raw_env(bool want_result) -> std::string {
872  kill_line();
873  if (!TL.empty()) {
874  parse_error(err_tok, "Verbatim-like environment in argument : ", get_cur_env_name(), "Verbatim-like environment in argument");
875  cur_tok.kill();
876  pop_level(bt_env);
877  return "";
878  }
879  mac_buffer.reset();

881  for (;;) {
882  if (is_verbatim_end()) break;
883  if (file_ended) {
884  bad_end_env(cl);
885  break;
886  }
887  if (want_result) {
888  mac_buffer.push_back(input_buffer.c_str());
889  mac_buffer.push_back('\n');
890  }
891  kill_line();
892  }
893  cur_tok.kill();
894  pop_level(bt_env);
895  return want_result ? mac_buffer.to_string() : "";
896 }

990 // This is done if we see a # while reading the body of a command.
991 // if exp is true, the token that follows the # is expanded,
992 void Parser::after_parameter(bool exp, size_t N) {
993  Token s = cur_tok;

1008  back_input(cur_tok);

1010 }

1021 auto Parser::group_to_string() -> std::string {

1086 // number of arguments for \newcommand; tries to be clever.
1087 auto Parser::read_mac_nbargs() -> size_t {
1088  TokenList L;
1089  read_optarg(L);
1090  if (!L.empty() && L.front().is_plus_token()) L.pop_front();
1091  while (!L.empty() && L.front().is_zero_token()) L.pop_front();
1092  if (L.empty()) return 0; // case of \newcommand\x[]{x}
1093  Token t = token_ns::get_unique(L);
1094  if (t.is_null()) {
1095  bad_nbargs(-1);
1096  return 0;
1097  }
1098  if (!t.is_a_char()) {
1099  bad_nbargs(-2);
1100  return 0;
1101  }
1102  if (t.cmd_val() == other_catcode) {
1103  auto tt = t.val_as_digit();
1104  if (tt >= 0 && tt <= 9) return tt;
1105  }
1106  bad_nbargs(-3);
1107  return 0;
1108 }

1110 // scans the `#1#2foo' part of \def\bar#1#2foo{}
1111 void Parser::get_def_nbargs(Macro *X, Token name) {
1112  def_type code = dt_normal;
1113  size_t nb = 0;
1114  TokenList L;
1115  scanner_status = ss_defining;
1116  for (;;) {
1117  if (get_token()) break; // will signal an error later
1118  if (cur_cmd_chr.is_parameter()) {
1119  if (get_token()) break;
1120  if (cur_cmd_chr.is_other() && cur_cmd_chr.chr == nb + '1') {
1121  X->set_delimiters(nb, L);
1122  L.clear();
1123  nb++;
1124  } else if (cur_cmd_chr.is_open_brace()) {
1125  code = dt_brace;
1126  L.push_back(cur_tok);
1127  break;
1128  } else
1129  bad_definition(name, nb);
1130  continue;
1131  }
1132  if (!cur_tok.is_a_char()) // \bgroup will not match here
1133  {
1134  code = dt_delim;
1135  L.push_back(cur_tok);
1136  continue;
1137  }
1138  if (cur_cmd_chr.cmd == open_catcode) break; // start of body
1139  if (cur_cmd_chr.cmd == close_catcode) break; // will signal an error later
1140  code = dt_delim;
1141  L.push_back(cur_tok);
1142  }
1143  scanner_status = ss_normal;
1144  X->set_delimiters(nb, L);
1145  X->set_nbargs(nb);
1146  X->set_type(code);
1147 }

1149 // Changes the type of a trivial macro.
1150 void Macro::correct_type() {
1151  if (type == dt_empty) type = dt_normal; // Is this needed ?
1152  if (type == dt_normal && body.empty() && nbargs == 0) type = dt_empty;
1153  if (type == dt_optional && nbargs > 1) {
1154  const TokenList &L = delimiters[1];
1155  auto A = L.begin();
1156  auto B = L.end();
1157  if (A == B) return;
1158  if (*A != the_parser.hash_table.dblarg_token) return;
1159  ++A;
1160  if (A != B) return;
1161  type = dt_spec_opt;
1162  }
1163 }

1197 // \newtheorem{name}{text}[c] case 1
1198 // \newtheorem{name}{text} case 2
1199 // \newtheorem{name}[c]{text} case 3
1200 // \newtheorem*{name}{text} case 4
1201 void Parser::M_new_thm() {
1202  bool star = remove_initial_star();
1203  std::string name = group_to_string();
1204  if (tracing_commands()) the_log << lg_startbracebs << "newtheorem " << name << lg_endbrace;
1205  TokenList ctr;
1206  int which_case = star ? 4 : 2;
1207  if (which_case == 2 && read_optarg_nopar(ctr)) which_case = 3;
1208  TokenList text = read_arg();
1209  if (which_case == 2 && read_optarg_nopar(ctr)) // ctr is empty here
1210  which_case = 1;
1211  // We have now read the arguments.
1212  Token y = find_env_token(name, true);
1213  err_tok = y; // replaces \newtheorem by \name
1214  if (!ok_to_define(y, rd_if_undef)) return;
1215  find_env_token(name, false);
1216  M_let_fast(cur_tok, hash_table.eth_token, true); // defines \endname
1217  Token thename_cmd;
1218  brace_me(text);
1219  if (which_case == 4) {
1220  text.push_back(hash_table.OB_token);
1221  text.push_back(hash_table.CB_token);
1222  } else {
1223  Thbuf1 << bf_reset << "the" << name;
1224  thename_cmd = hash_table.locate(Thbuf1);
1225  M_let_fast(thename_cmd, hash_table.relax_token, true); // in case of error
1226  text.push_back(thename_cmd);
1227  }
1228  TokenList aux = toks_registers[theorem_bodyfont_code].val;
1229  brace_me(aux);
1230  text.splice(text.end(), aux);
1231  aux = token_ns::string_to_list(name, true);
1232  text.splice(text.end(), aux);
1233  if (which_case == 3) {
1234  aux = ctr;
1235  brace_me(aux);
1236  } else
1237  aux = token_ns::string_to_list(name, true);
1238  text.splice(text.end(), aux);
1239  aux = toks_registers[theorem_style_code].val;
1240  brace_me(aux);
1241  text.splice(text.end(), aux);
1242  text.push_front(hash_table.bth_token);
1243  new_macro(text, y, true); // This defines \name
1244  if (which_case == 4) return;
1245  if (which_case == 3) {
1246  if (csname_ctr(ctr, Thbuf1)) {
1247  bad_counter0();
1248  return;
1249  }
1250  if (counter_check(Thbuf1, false)) return; // checks the counter
1251  Thbuf2 << bf_reset << "the" << (Thbuf1.c_str() + 2);
1252  cur_tok = hash_table.locate(Thbuf2);
1253  TokenList R;
1254  R.push_back(cur_tok);
1255  new_macro(R, thename_cmd, true);
1256  return;
1257  }
1258  TokenList the_value = token_ns::string_to_list(name, true);
1259  TokenList V = the_value;
1260  the_value.push_front(hash_table.arabic_token);
1261  if (which_case == 2) {
1262  back_input(hash_table.relax_token);
1263  } else {
1264  back_input(Token(other_t_offset, ']'));

1349 // Returns all tokens before the \end at level zero
1350 void Parser::grab_env(TokenList &v) {
1351  int b = 1;
1352  int elevel = 0;
1353  for (;;) {
1354  if (get_token()) {
1355  parse_error(err_tok, "End of data reached while scanning content of ", get_cur_env_name(), "bad grab env");
1356  return;
1357  }
1358  if (check_brace(b)) {
1359  parse_error(err_tok, "Spurious close brace removed");
1360  ++b;
1361  continue;
1362  }
1363  if (b == 1 && cur_cmd_chr.cmd == begin_cmd) elevel++;
1364  if (b == 1 && cur_cmd_chr.cmd == end_cmd) {
1365  if (elevel == 0) {
1366  back_input();
1367  return;
1368  }
1369  elevel--;
1370  }
1371  v.push_back(cur_tok);
1372  }
1373 }

1403 // Macro expansion ------------------------------
1404 
1405 // This is macro_call in TeX
1406 // Assumes that cur_tok holds the macro name, the argument the value.
1407 void Parser::expand_mac(Macro &X) {
1408  if (tracing_macros()) the_log << lg_start << " " << X << lg_end;
1409  def_type spec = X.type;
1410  if (spec == dt_empty) return;
1411  if (skip_prefix(X[0])) return;
1412  bool optional = spec == dt_optional || spec == dt_spec_opt;
1413  bool spec_optional = spec == dt_spec_opt;
1414  auto n = X.nbargs;
1415  TokenList arguments[10];
1416  for (size_t i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
1417  if (spec == dt_delim || spec == dt_brace) {
1418  if (!X[i].empty()) {
1419  if (scan_group_del(arguments[i], X[i])) return;
1420  } else if (scan_group2(arguments[i]))
1421  return;
1422  } else if (!optional) {
1423  if (scan_group2(arguments[i])) return;
1424  } else {
1425  optional = false;
1426  TokenList u;
1427  bool have_arg = false;
1428  if (scan_group_opt(u, have_arg)) return;
1429  if (have_arg)
1430  arguments[i] = u;
1431  else {
1432  if (spec_optional) { // value of #1 defaults to #2 which is scanned here
1433  if (scan_group2(arguments[1])) return;
1434  i++;
1435  arguments[2] = arguments[1];
1436  } else
1437  arguments[1] = X[1];
1438  }
1439  }
1440  if (tracing_macros()) the_log << "#" << i << "<-" << arguments[i] << lg_end;
1441  }
1442  TokenList res = expand_mac_inner(X.body, arguments);
1443  if (spec == dt_brace) res.push_back(hash_table.OB_token);
1444  back_input(res);
1445 }

1447 // This is the code that replaces arguments by values in the body.
1448 // note that Tex uses a completely different method (there is a stack with
1449 // all arguments of all macros; here we have just one table).
1450 auto Parser::expand_mac_inner(const TokenList &W, TokenList *arguments) -> TokenList {
1451  auto C = W.begin();
1452  auto E = W.end();
1453  TokenList res;
1454  while (C != E) {
1455  Token x = *C;
1456  ++C;
1457  if (x.is_a_char() && x.cmd_val() == eol_catcode) {
1458  int k = x.chr_val();
1459  TokenList ww = arguments[k];
1460  res.splice(res.end(), ww);
1461  } else
1462  res.push_back(x);
1463  }
1464  return res;
1465 }

1719 void Parser::E_while(subtypes cc) {

1825 // if def is false, check that \c@foo=2 is OK
1826 // otherwise, checks that \c@foo is undefined or relax
1827 // Returns true if bad
1828 auto Parser::counter_check(Buffer &b, bool def) -> bool {
1829  cur_tok = hash_table.locate(b);
1830  Equivalent &E = hash_table.eqtb[cur_tok.eqtb_loc()];
1831  if (def) {
1832  if (!E.is_undef_or_relax()) {
1833  bad_redefinition(0, cur_tok);
1834  return true;
1835  }
1836  } else {
1837  if (E.get_cmd() != assign_int_cmd) {
1838  bad_counter1(b, E);
1839  return true;
1840  }
1841  }
1842  return false;
1843 }

1845 // Reads an optional argument bar; puts \cl@bar in cur_tok
1846 // Return 0 if no opt argument, 1 if error, 2 if OK
1847 // If s is a valid string, it contains the optional argument
1848 
1849 auto Parser::counter_read_opt(String s) -> int {
1850  if (s != nullptr) {
1851  if (s[0] == 0) return 0; // s empty says no opt arg
1852  Buffer &b = Thbuf2;
1853  b << bf_reset << "cl@" << s;
1854  finish_csname(b, "newcounter");
1855  return 2;
1856  }
1857  TokenList bar_list;
1858  int ne = main_ns::nb_errs;
1859  if (!read_optarg_nopar(bar_list)) return 0;
1860  if (ne != main_ns::nb_errs) return 1;
1861  if (my_csname("cl@", "", bar_list, "newcounter_opt")) return 1;
1862  return 2;
1863 }

1865 // This defines a new counter, named name; second arg is for counter_read_opt
1866 // cur_tok (o be read again) holds the token \c@foo
1867 auto Parser::counter_aux(const std::string &name, String opt, Token T) -> bool {
1868  Buffer &b = Thbuf1;
1869  // We are defining a counter now
1870  // We construct a macro without argument that expands to \number\c@foo
1871  TokenList L;
1872  L.push_front(cur_tok);
1873  L.push_front(hash_table.number_token);
1874 
1875  // evaluate : \global\let\cl@foo\@empty
1876  b << bf_reset << "cl@" << name; // b is now cl@foo
1877  M_let_fast(hash_table.locate(b), hash_table.empty_token, true);
1878 
1879  // thexx_cmd is the token associated to \thefoo
1880  b << bf_reset << "the" << name; // B is now thefoo
1881  Token thecmd = hash_table.locate(b);
1882  cur_tok = T; // in case of overflow, this gives the correct message
1883  new_constant(newcount_code); // this will eat the \c@foo token
1884  new_macro(L, thecmd, true);
1885  switch (counter_read_opt(opt)) {
1886  case 0: return false;
1887  case 1: return true;
1888  default: break;
1889  }
1890  // evaluate: \xdef\cl@bar{\cl@bar\noexpand\@elt{foo}}
1891  // We know that \cl@bar can be expanded only once.
1892  TokenList foo_list = token_ns::string_to_list(name, true);
1893  Token cl_token = cur_tok; // \cl@bar
1894  get_token(); // get the \cl@bar token
1895  M_cons(cl_token, foo_list);
1896  return false;
1897 }

1929 // Arguments: a command like "chardef", max value, a subtype like newwrite_code
1930 // and a symcode like char_given_cmd
1931 // allocates registter number k whose value at the table at position alloc_pos
1932 // (plus an offset, maybe)
1933 void Parser::new_constant(String name, int max_val, subtypes alloc_pos, symcodes c) {
1934  Token T = cur_tok;
1935  get_r_token(true);
1936  int k = allocation_table[alloc_pos];
1937  if (k >= max_val) {
1938  err_buf << bf_reset << "Overflow in " << T << "; max value is " << max_val;
1939  signal_error(T, "allocation overflow");
1940  return;
1941  }
1942  ++k;
1943  if (k == 255 && c == assign_int_cmd) ++k;
1944  allocation_table[alloc_pos] = k;
1945  if (c == assign_int_cmd) k += count_reg_offset;
1946  if (c == assign_mu_glue_cmd) k += muskip_reg_offset;
1947  CmdChr R(c, subtypes(k));
1948  eq_define(cur_tok.eqtb_loc(), R, true);
1949  the_log << lg_startbracebs << name << " " << cur_tok << "=\\" << R.name() << lg_endbrace;

1952 // c is the code of \value, \stepcounter, \addtocounter, \setcounter, or
1953 // \@stpelt
1954 // This may generate \calc{\global\advance\c@foo} for \addtocounter{foo}
1955 // or \global\advance\c@foo 25\relax for \addtocounter{foo}{25}
1956 // In the case of \stepcounter, we do
1957 // \global\advance\c@foo\@one\let\elt@stpelt\cl@foo
1958 void Parser::E_counter(int c) {
1959  Token first = cur_tok;
1960  if (c == addtoreset_code) {
1961  E_addtoreset();
1962  return;
1963  }
1964  if (M_counter(false)) return;
1965  if (c == value_code) return;
1966  get_token();
1967  Token t = cur_tok; // we have \c@foo
1968  TokenList L;
1969  if (!calc_loaded && c != stepcounter_code && c != killcounter_code) L = read_arg();
1970  L.push_front(t);
1971  if (c != setcounter_code && c != killcounter_code) L.push_front(hash_table.advance_token);
1972  L.push_front(hash_table.global_token);
1973  if (c == stepcounter_code) {
1974  L.push_back(hash_table.at_one_token);
1975  L.push_back(hash_table.let_token);
1976  L.push_back(hash_table.elt_token);
1977  L.push_back(hash_table.killcounter_token);
1978  group_buffer << bf_reset << "cl@" << (hash_table[t.hash_loc()] + 2);
1979  t = hash_table.locate(group_buffer);
1980  // L.push_back(hash_table.OB_token);
1981  L.push_back(t);
1982  // L.push_back(hash_table.CB_token);
1983  } else if (c == killcounter_code)
1984  L.push_back(hash_table.at_zero_token);
1985  else if (calc_loaded) {
1986  brace_me(L);
1987  L.push_front(hash_table.calc_token);
1988  } else
1989  L.push_back(hash_table.relax_token);
1990  finish_counter_cmd(first, L);
1991 }

2370  E_scan_up_down(df_up, df_down, w, cmd);

2372  back_input(cmd);

2375 void Parser::E_scan_up_down(TokenList &A, TokenList &B, TokenList &C, TokenList &res) {
2376  back_input(hash_table.relax_token); // end marker
2377  back_input(C);
2378  TokenList df_up = A;
2379  TokenList df_down = B;
2380  get_token();
2381  if (cur_cmd_chr.is_single_quote()) {
2382  scan_prime();
2383  get_token();
2384  }
2385  if (cur_cmd_chr.cmd == hat_catcode) {
2386  df_up = read_arg();
2387  get_token();
2388  if (cur_cmd_chr.cmd == underscore_catcode) {
2389  df_down = read_arg();
2390  } else
2391  back_input();
2392  } else if (cur_cmd_chr.cmd == underscore_catcode) {
2393  df_down = read_arg();
2394  get_token();
2395  if (cur_cmd_chr.is_single_quote()) {
2396  scan_prime();
2397  get_token();
2398  }
2399  if (cur_cmd_chr.cmd == hat_catcode) {
2400  df_up = read_arg();
2401  } else
2402  back_input();
2403  } else
2404  back_input();
2405  read_until(hash_table.relax_token); // read all unused tokens
2406  brace_me(df_up);
2407  brace_me(df_down);
2408  res.splice(res.end(), df_down);
2409  res.splice(res.end(), df_up);
2410 }

2412 // Implements \sideset
2413 void Parser::E_sideset() {
2414  TokenList A = read_arg();
2415  TokenList B = read_arg();
2416  TokenList C = read_arg();
2417  TokenList none;
2418  none.push_back(hash_table.mmlnone_token);
2419  if (A.empty() && B.empty()) {
2420  } // \mathop{C}\limits
2421  else {
2422  if (!B.empty()) E_scan_up_down(none, none, B, C);
2423  if (!A.empty()) {

2571 // If the tokens that follows are that of the string S (upper or lower case)
2572 // then they are read. Initial spaces are read. Full expansion.
2573 auto Parser::scan_keyword(String s) -> bool {
2574  size_t k = 0;
2575  TokenList L;
2576  for (;;) {
2577  if (s[k] == 0) return true;
2578  get_x_token();
2579  if (cur_tok.not_a_cmd() && (cur_cmd_chr.char_val() == uchar(s[k]) || cur_cmd_chr.char_val() == uchar(s[k] + 'A' - 'a'))) {
2580  L.push_back(cur_tok);
2581  k++;
2582  } else if (L.empty() && cur_cmd_chr.is_space())
2583  continue;
2584  else {
2585  back_input();
2586  back_input(L);
2587  return false;
2588  }
2589  }

2791 // Find \fi, \else , \or at level zero.
2792 void Parser::pass_text(Token Tfe) {
2793  int l = 0;
2794  SaveScannerStatus foo(ss_skipping);
2795  for (;;) {
2796  if (get_token()) {
2797  cur_tok = hash_table.fi_token;
2798  cur_cmd_chr = CmdChr(fi_or_else_cmd, fi_code);
2799  lost_if(Tfe, conditions.top_line());
2800  return;
2801  }
2802  if (cur_cmd_chr.cmd == fi_or_else_cmd) {
2803  trace_if(l);
2804  if (l == 0) return;
2805  if (cur_cmd_chr.chr == fi_code) l--;
2806  } else if (cur_cmd_chr.cmd == if_test_cmd || cur_cmd_chr.cmd == fpif_cmd) {
2807  l++;
2808  trace_if(l);
2809  }
2810  }

2839 // This is called when we see \fi \or \else, and don't expect it via
2840 // pass_text. If it's an \else, we call pass_text to get the \fi.
2841 // the codes are, in order: if_code,fi_code,else_code,or_code.
2842 
2843 void Parser::E_fi_or_else() {
2844  Token T = cur_tok;
2845  trace_if(0);
2846  if (conditions.empty()) {
2847  extra_fi_or_else();
2848  return;
2849  }
2850  int K = conditions.top_limit();
2851  if (K == if_code)
2852  insert_relax();
2853  else if (cur_cmd_chr.chr > K)
2854  extra_fi_or_else();
2855  else {
2856  while (cur_cmd_chr.chr != fi_code) pass_text(T);
2857  conditions.pop();
2858  }
2859 }

2871 void Parser::E_if_test(subtypes test, bool negate) {
2872  Token Tfe = cur_tok;
2873  auto sz = conditions.push(negate ? test + unless_code : test);
2874  int k = conditions.top_serial();
2875  trace_if(negate ? -1 : -2);
2876  if (test == if_case_code) {
2877  auto n = scan_int(cur_tok);
2878  trace_if("\\ifcase", k, n);
2879  while (n != 0) {
2880  pass_text(Tfe);
2881  if (conditions.is_this_if(sz)) {
2882  if (cur_cmd_chr.chr == or_code)
2883  n--;
2884  else if (cur_cmd_chr.chr == fi_code) {
2885  trace_if("\\ifcase", k, "failed");
2886  conditions.pop();
2887  return;
2888  } else {
2889  trace_if("\\ifcase", k, "choose else");
2890  conditions.wait_for_fi();
2891  return;
2892  }
2893  } else if (cur_cmd_chr.chr == fi_code)
2894  conditions.pop();
2895  }
2896  conditions.set_limit(sz, or_code);
2897  trace_if("\\ifcase", k, "found");
2898  return;
2899  }
2900  bool b = eval_condition(test);
2901  if (negate) b = !b;
2902  trace_if("iftest", k, boolean(b));
2903  if (b) {
2904  conditions.set_limit(sz, else_code);
2905  return;
2906  }
2907  for (;;) {
2908  pass_text(Tfe);
2909  if (conditions.is_this_if(sz)) {
2910  if (cur_cmd_chr.chr != or_code) break;
2911 
2912  extra_fi_or_else();
2913  } else if (cur_cmd_chr.chr == fi_code)
2914  conditions.pop();
2915  }
2916  if (cur_cmd_chr.chr == fi_code)
2917  conditions.pop();
2918  else
2919  conditions.wait_for_fi();
2920 }

2922 // Returns the truth value of the next condition
2923 auto Parser::eval_condition(subtypes test) -> bool {
2924  switch (test) {
2925  case if_true_code: return true;
2926  case if_false_code: return false;
2927  case ifx_code: return E_ifx();
2928  case if_char_code:
2929  case if_cat_code: {
2930  symcodes a1, a2;
2931  subtypes b1, b2;
2932  get_x_token_or_active_char(a1, b1);
2933  get_x_token_or_active_char(a2, b2);
2934  if (test == if_char_code) return b1 == b2;
2935  return a1 == a2;
2936  }
2937  case if_odd_code: {
2938  auto k = scan_int(cur_tok);
2939  return (k & 1) == 1;
2940  }
2941  case if_leapyear_code: return tralics_ns::is_leap_year(scan_braced_int(cur_tok));
2942  case if_int_code:
2943  case if_dim_code: {
2944  Token T = cur_tok;
2945  if (test == if_int_code)
2946  scan_int(T);
2947  else
2948  scan_dimen(false, T);
2949  auto n = cur_val.get_int_val();
2950  remove_initial_space();
2951  auto r = cur_tok.val_as_other();
2952  if (r == '=' || r == '<' || r == '>') {
2953  } else {
2954  r = '=';
2955  missing_equals(T);
2956  }
2957  if (test == if_int_code)
2958  scan_int(T);
2959  else
2960  scan_dimen(false, T);
2961  if (r == '<') return n < cur_val.get_int_val();
2962  if (r == '>') return n > cur_val.get_int_val();
2963  return n == cur_val.get_int_val();
2964  }
2965  case if_mmode_code: return the_stack.get_mode() == mode_math;
2966  case if_vmode_code: return the_stack.in_v_mode();
2967  case if_hmode_code: return the_stack.in_h_mode();
2968  case if_eof_code: return is_input_open();
2969  case if_csname_code: fetch_name2(); return hash_table.is_defined(fetch_name_res);
2970  case if_defined_code: {
2971  SaveScannerStatus tmp(ss_normal);
2972  get_token();
2973  return !cur_cmd_chr.is_undef();
2974  }
2975  case if_fontchar_code: {
2976  auto k = scan_font_ident();
2977  scan_char_num(); // pretend all chars are in the font
2978  return k != 0;
2979  }
2980  case if_void_code: {
2981  auto n = scan_reg_num();
2982  Xml *x = box_table[n].get_val();
2983  if (x == nullptr) return true;
2984  return x->empty();
2985  }
2986  case if_hbox_code:
2987  case if_vbox_code: scan_reg_num(); return false; // pretend it's neither H nor V
2988  case if_inner_code:
2989  if (the_stack.get_mode() == mode_math) return is_inner_math();
2990  return false;
2991  default: return false;
2992  }
2993 }

3492 void Parser::do_register_command(bool gbl) {
3493  Token T = cur_tok;
3494  int q = cur_cmd_chr.cmd;
3495  int p;
3496  auto l = do_register_arg(q, p, T); // changes T from \advance to \skip
3497  if (cur_tok.is_invalid()) return; // was an error
3498  if (q == register_cmd)
3499  scan_optional_equals();
3500  else
3501  scan_keyword("by");
3502  if (q < multiply_cmd) { // advance or set.
3503  if (p < it_glue) {
3504  if (p == it_int)
3505  scan_int(T);
3506  else
3507  scan_dimen(false, T);
3508  if (q == advance_cmd) {
3509  if (p == it_int)
3510  cur_val.incr_int(eqtb_int_table[l].val);
3511  else
3512  cur_val.incr_dim(eqtb_dim_table[l].get_val());
3513  }
3514  } else {
3515  scan_glue(internal_type(p), T);
3516  if (q == advance_cmd) cur_val.incr_glue(glue_table[l].get_val());
3517  }
3518  } else {
3519  auto v = scan_int(T); // Here we need an integer.
3520  if (p < it_glue) {
3521  if (p == it_int)
3522  cur_val.set_int(eqtb_int_table[l].val);
3523  else
3524  cur_val.set_dim(eqtb_dim_table[l].get_val());
3525  ScaledInt &W = cur_val.get_scaled();
3526  if (q == multiply_cmd)
3527  if (p == it_int)
3528  W.mult_integer(v);
3529  else
3530  W.mult_scaled(v);
3531  else { // division
3532  W.divide(v);
3533  }
3534  } else {
3535  Glue s = glue_table[l].get_val();
3536  if (q == multiply_cmd)
3537  s.multiply(cur_val.get_int_val());
3538  else
3539  s.divide(cur_val.get_int_val());
3540  cur_val.set_glue_val(s);
3541  }
3542  }
3543  if (p == it_dimen)
3544  dim_define(l, cur_val.get_dim_val(), gbl);
3545  else if (p < it_glue)
3546  word_define(l, cur_val.get_int_val(), gbl);
3547  else
3548  glue_define(l, cur_val.get_glue_val(), gbl);
3549 }

3562 // This implements \arabic, \@arabic, etc

3697 // This returns true if the ifthenelse condition should be true.
3698 // is recursive...
3699 auto Parser::T_ifthenelse_inner(Token t) -> bool {
3700  bool res = true;
3701  bool must_negate = false;
3702  for (;;) {
3703  if (get_token()) break; // seen the end
3704  Token x = cur_tok;
3705  if (x.is_space_token() || cur_cmd_chr.is_relax()) continue;
3706  if (tracing_commands()) the_log << lg_startif << x << lg_endbrace;
3707  if (x == hash_table.not_token || x == hash_table.NOT_token) {
3708  must_negate = !must_negate;
3709  continue;
3710  }
3711  if (x.is_bs_oparen()) {
3712  res = T_ifthenelse_inner(t);
3713  skip_over_parens();
3714  } else if (x == hash_table.isodd_token) {
3715  TokenList L = read_arg();
3716  back_input(hash_table.relax_token);
3717  back_input(L);
3718  auto n = scan_int(x);
3719  res = (n & 1) != 0;
3720  } else if (x == hash_table.isundefined_token) {
3721  TokenList L = read_arg();
3722  if (L.empty())
3723  res = false;
3724  else {
3725  Token target = L.front();
3726  token_from_list(target);
3727  res = cur_cmd_chr.is_undef();
3728  }
3729  } else if (x == hash_table.lengthtest_token) {
3730  TokenList L = read_arg();
3731  back_input(hash_table.relax_token);
3732  back_input(L);
3733  cur_tok = t;
3734  res = eval_condition(if_dim_code);
3735  } else if (x == hash_table.boolean_token) {
3736  TokenList L = read_arg();
3737  if (my_csname("if", "", L, "boolean"))
3738  res = false;
3739  else {
3740  get_token();
3741  res = cur_cmd_chr.cmd == if_test_cmd && cur_cmd_chr.chr == if_true_code;
3742  }
3743  } else if (x == hash_table.equal_token) {
3744  TokenList L1 = read_arg();
3745  TokenList L2 = read_arg();
3746  cur_tok = t;
3747  read_toks_edef(L1);
3748  cur_tok = t;
3749  read_toks_edef(L2);
3750  res = L1 == L2;
3751  if (tracing_commands()) the_log << lg_startif << "equal " << boolean(res) << lg_endbrace;
3752  } else {
3753  back_input();
3754  cur_tok = t;
3755  res = eval_condition(if_int_code);
3756  }
3757  break;
3758  }
3759  if (must_negate) res = !res;
3760  for (;;) { // we have the value. Look at what remains.
3761  if (get_token()) break; // seen the end
3762  Token x = cur_tok;
3763  if (x.is_space_token() || cur_cmd_chr.is_relax()) continue;
3764  if (x.is_bs_cparen()) {
3765  back_input(x);
3766  break;
3767  }
3768  if (x == hash_table.or_token || x == hash_table.OR_token) {
3769  if (tracing_commands()) the_log << lg_startif << "\\or " << skip_or_continue(res) << lg_endbrace;
3770  if (res) break;
3771  return T_ifthenelse_inner(t);
3772  }
3773  if (x == hash_table.and_token || x == hash_table.AND_token) {
3774  if (tracing_commands()) the_log << lg_startif << "\\and " << skip_or_continue(!res) << lg_endbrace;
3775  if (!res) return false;
3776  return T_ifthenelse_inner(t);
3777  }
3778  break;
3779  }
3780  if (tracing_commands()) the_log << lg_startif << "-> " << boolean(res) << lg_endbrace;
3781  return res;
3782 }

3826 // This computes num/den with 6 decimals (why not use C++ code ?)
3827 // and constructs \pm(tmp+f/2^16)
3828 // After that, we multiply.
3829 void Parser::calc_ratio_eval(long num, long den, SthInternal &res) {
3830  static const unsigned int my_max = ((1U << 31) - 1);
3831  RealNumber val;
3832  if (num < 0) {
3833  val.set_negative(true);
3834  num = -num;
3835  }
3836  if (den < 0) {
3837  val.change_sign();
3838  den = -den;
3839  }
3840  while (den >= int(my_max / 10)) {
3841  den /= 2;
3842  num /= 2;
3843  }
3844  if (den == 0) {
3845  parse_error(hash_table.calc_token, "Division by zero");
3846  return;
3847  }
3848  auto A = num / den;
3849  val.set_ipart(A); // Integer part of the thing.
3850  long table[17];
3851  for (int k = 0; k < 10; k++) {
3852  num -= A * den;
3853  num *= 10;
3854  A = num / den;
3855  table[k] = A;
3856  }
3857  val.convert_decimal_part(10, table);
3858  calc_spec_mul(val, res);
3859 }

3904 // This is the big function
3905 void Parser::calc_aux(SthInternal &A) {
3906  skip_initial_space_and_back_input();
3907  calc_primitive(A);
3908  for (;;) {
3909  skip_initial_space();
3910  Token T = cur_tok; // what next ?
3911  if (T.is_exclam_token()) return; // special end marker.
3912  if (T.is_close_paren()) return;
3913  if (T.is_plus_token() || T.is_minus_token()) {
3914  if (tracing_commands()) the_log << lg_startcalc << "+-" << lg_endbrace;
3915  SthInternal B;
3916  B.initialise(A.get_type());
3917  calc_primitive(B);
3918  if (T.is_minus_token()) B.negate();
3919  A.add(B);
3920  continue;
3921  }
3922  if (tracing_commands()) the_log << lg_startcalc << "*/" << lg_endbrace;
3923  if (!(T.is_star_token() || T.is_slash_token())) {
3924  parse_error(hash_table.calc_token, "unexpected token in calc\n", T.tok_to_str(), "unexpected in calc");
3925  return;
3926  }
3927  bool mul = T.is_star_token();
3928  skip_initial_space();
3929  T = cur_tok;
3930  if (T == hash_table.ratio_token) {
3931  TokenList x = read_arg();
3932  TokenList y = read_arg();
3933  if (mul)
3934  ratio_evaluate(x, y, A);
3935  else
3936  ratio_evaluate(y, x, A);
3937  continue;
3938  }
3939  if (T == hash_table.real_token) {
3940  if (!mul) { // special case 3 / \real{1.5} ...
3941  TokenList x = read_arg();
3942  x.push_back(Token(other_t_offset, 'p'));
3943  x.push_back(Token(other_t_offset, 't'));
3944  TokenList y; // empty
3945  ratio_evaluate(y, x, A);
3946  continue;
3947  } // case 3 * \real{1.5}
3948  calc_mul_aux(A);
3949  continue;
3950  }
3951  // Could be anything, says (2+3)*(4+5);
3952  // Must be an integer...
3953  SthInternal aux;
3954  aux.initialise(it_int);
3955  back_input();
3956  calc_primitive(aux);
3957  auto v = aux.get_int_val();
3958  if (mul) {
3959  if (A.is_glue())
3960  A.glue_multiply(v);
3961  else if (A.is_int())
3962  A.get_scaled().mult_integer(v);
3963  else
3964  A.get_scaled().mult_scaled(v);
3965  } else {
3966  if (A.is_glue())
3967  A.glue_divide(v);
3968  else
3969  A.get_scaled().divide(v);
3970  }
3971  }
3972 }

4097  else if (pos == xmlB_location)

4101  Xml * Y = new Xml(p, res);

4104

4111 // This function is called from scan_box, see above,
4112 // or \box\copy\usebox\hbox etc, src is 2M in these cases
4113 // In some cases, the box is already there, and the code is easy.
4114 // Otherwise we push a continuation on the stack.
4115 
4116 void Parser::begin_box(size_t src, subtypes c) {
4117  Token T = cur_tok;
4118  size_t res;
4119  Xml * cur_box = nullptr;
4120  if (c == usebox_code) { // a variant of \copy with an argument
4121  leave_v_mode();
4122  TokenList L = read_arg();
4123  back_input(hash_table.relax_token);
4124  back_input(L);
4125  c = copy_code;
4126  }
4127  if (c == box_code) {
4128  res = scan_reg_num();
4129  cur_box = box_table[res].get_val();
4130  box_table[res].set_val(nullptr);
4131  box_end(cur_box, src);
4132  return;
4133  }
4134  if (c == copy_code) {
4135  res = scan_reg_num();
4136  cur_box = box_table[res].get_val();
4137  box_end(cur_box, src);
4138  return;
4139  }
4140  if (c == lastbox_code) {
4141  flush_buffer();
4142  cur_box = the_stack.top_stack()->last_box();
4143  box_end(cur_box, src);
4144  return;
4145  }
4146  if (c == useboxA_code || c == useboxB_code) {
4147  cur_box = (c == useboxA_code ? the_xmlA : the_xmlB);
4148  if (cur_box != nullptr)
4149  cur_box = cur_box->deep_copy();
4150  else
4151  cur_box = new Xml(Istring(""), nullptr);
4152  box_end(cur_box, src);
4153  return;
4154  }
4155  if (c == useboxB_code) {
4156  cur_box = the_stack.top_stack()->last_box();
4157  box_end(cur_box, src);
4158  return;
4159  }
4160  if (c == vsplit_code) {
4161  scan_reg_num();
4162  scan_keyword("to");
4163  scan_dimen(false, T);
4164  box_end(cur_box, src);
4165  return;
4166  }
4167  flush_buffer();
4168  auto box_name = Istring("");
4169  if (c == parbox_code) {
4170  // same arguments as minipage
4171  ignore_optarg(); // position
4172  ignore_optarg(); // height
4173  ignore_optarg(); // inner_pos
4174  scan_glue(it_glue, T, false); // width
4175  } else if (c == xbox_code)
4176  box_name = nT_arg_nopar();
4177  else if (c == marginpar_code) {
4178  ignore_optarg();
4179  box_name = the_names[np_marginpar];
4180  } else if (scan_keyword("to") || scan_keyword("spread"))
4181  scan_dimen(false, T);
4182  if (tracing_commands()) {
4183  the_log << lg_startbrace;
4184  if (box_name.empty())
4185  the_log << "Constructing an anonymous box" << lg_endbrace;
4186  else
4187  the_log << "Constructing a box named " << box_name << lg_endbrace;
4188  }
4189  scan_left_brace();
4190  push_level(bt_brace);
4191  TokenList L;
4192  if (c == xbox_code)
4193  L = toks_registers[everyxbox_code].val;
4194  else if (c == vbox_code)
4195  L = toks_registers[everyvbox_code].val;
4196  else if (c == vtop_code)
4197  L = toks_registers[everyvbox_code].val;
4198  else if (c == hbox_code)
4199  L = toks_registers[everyhbox_code].val;
4200  if (!L.empty()) {
4201  if (tracing_commands()) {
4202  String name = "<everyvbox> ";
4203  if (c == xbox_code)
4204  name = "<everyxbox> ";
4205  else if (c == hbox_code)
4206  name = "<everyhbox> ";
4207  the_log << lg_startbrace << name << L << lg_endbrace;
4208  }
4209  back_input(L);
4210  }
4211  Xml * cur_boxa = the_stack.push_hbox(box_name);
4212  SaveAux *x = new SaveAuxBoxend(src, cur_boxa);
4213  push_save_stack(x);
4214  the_stack.set_arg_mode();
4215 }

4284 // Code of \long, \def, etc. Handles \globaldefs
4285 // This is called an assignment, so \afterassignment is completed here
4286 void Parser::M_prefixed() {
4287  int flags = 0;
4288  while (cur_cmd_chr.cmd == prefix_cmd) {
4289  flags |= cur_cmd_chr.chr;
4290  remove_initial_space_relax();
4291  }
4292  bool b_global = false;
4293  if (flags >= 8) {
4294  flags -= 8;
4295  b_global = true;
4296  }
4297  auto K = symcodes(user_cmd + flags);
4298  symcodes C = cur_cmd_chr.cmd;
4299  if (C <= max_non_prefixed_command) {
4300  if (b_global || (flags != 0)) prefix_error(b_global, K);
4301  if (cur_tok.is_valid()) back_input(); // case of prefix at end of list
4302  return;
4303  }
4304  if (C != def_cmd && (flags != 0)) prefix_error(b_global, K);
4305  // look at \globaldefs
4306  auto gd = eqtb_int_table[globaldefs_code].val;
4307  if (gd > 0) b_global = true;
4308  if (gd < 0) b_global = false;
4309  if (tracing_commands() && (b_global || (flags != 0))) {
4310  the_log << lg_startbrace;
4311  trace_buffer.reset();
4312  trace_buffer.dump_prefix(true, b_global, K);
4313  the_log << trace_buffer << cur_tok << lg_endbrace;
4314  }
4315  if (C == let_cmd)
4316  M_let(cur_cmd_chr.chr, b_global);
4317  else if (C == def_cmd)
4318  define_something(cur_cmd_chr.chr, b_global, K);
4319  else
4320  M_prefixed_aux(b_global);
4321  Token aat = get_after_ass_tok();
4322  if (!aat.is_null()) {
4323  back_input(aat);
4324  if (tracing_commands()) the_log << lg_startbrace << "after assignment: " << aat << lg_endbrace;
4325  }
4326 }
